<TITLE> EC asks Khaleda not to campaign </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 18 (bdnews24.com)  The chief election commissioner has asked opposition leader Khaleda Zia to not campaign for her candidates in the Apr 2 by-elections to seats vacated by MPs. ATM Shamsul Huda sent a letter to the BNP chief by a special courier Tuesday night, deputy secretary at the Election Commission secretariat, Mihir Sarwar Morshed, told bdnews24.com The polls chief also asked prime minister Sheikh Hasina in a letter on Mar 8 to not start campaigning which officially begins Thursday. The electoral law says no ministers, state ministers, deputy ministers or the leader and deputy leader of parliament and opposition, and whips who equal a minister in status cannot do polls campaign. Rangpur-3 and 6, Kurigram-2, Bigra-6 and 7, and Kishoreganj-6 constituencies, vacated by the president, prime minister, opposition leader and Jatiya Party chairman who won more than one seat, are scheduled to go to by-polls. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina's cousin Shekh Helal Uddin has been elected uncontested to Bagerhat-1 seat.
